summary:
Inspiring, empowering and results driven people manager, business developer, partnership developer, organizational advisor and facilitator in a multicultural and multi-stakeholder international environment. Focussed on long term goals, next to realizing practical quick wins. 

Skills:
•	Develop strategic direction of the organisation, leading inspiring processes, building on knowledge of internal and external stakeholders, as well as operational planning to ensure implementation of the strategic direction;
•	Translation of research, new technology and promising practices into practical concepts (business cases), prototype and bring to scale proven to be of interest to funders (donors, investors, private sector);
•	Establish multi- disciplinary partnerships for change in high complex environment with Government, Civil Society, Communities, Private Sector, Associations, UN agencies, Research Institutes, Investors and Donors;
•	Transform professional teams by working from core competences, talent and energy 

Expertise:
Public health, health and community systems strenghtening, HIV, SRHR and STIs in developing countries, key populations, women, youth and children issues, essential drugs and medical supplies procurement and supply chain management in Africa, Dutch non-governmental organisation.

