Responsibilities:
•	Direct reports 4 professionals being Head of Programmes and Knowledge, 2 Country Representatives, Communication Manager, but first year 6 direct reports being 2 Programme Manager, M&E and Research Manager; M&E Officer, Communication Manager, Programme Officer;
•	Provide thought leadership of PATA in collaboration with the Executive Director to ensure programmes, plans and budgets align with strategic plan and annual plans; 
•	Strengthen PATA governance and organisational development;
•	Delegate, empower, manage and oversee performance of senior programme staff, provide consistent supervision, mentorship and development; 
•	Develop a strengthened portfolio of projects that address the gaps and needs of adolescent and paediatric HIV to attract new funders resulting in sustainable pipeline of funds and expand funding base as set in the strategic plan;
•	Build, strengthen and nurture positive relations with donors, strategic partners, consortia and working groups as a thought leader in the sector.

Head of Executive Office Medicins Sans Frontieres Operational Centre Amsterdam (OCA) (September 2018 – now)

Responsibilities:
•	Direct reports 6 professionals (strategic plan coordinator, internal communication advisor, executive assistants, business intelligence officer) and 2 managers (Responsible Behaviour Unit and Project Management Organization);
•	Strategic sparring partner and support of the OCA MT, especially the Chair of the OCA MT/ GD MSF- Holland (‘right-hand’ role);
•	Supporting the decision-making process of the OCA-MT: 1) Ensuring coherent translation of strategy to implementation; 2) Aligning and setting agendas of the different layers of management platforms; 3) Influencing agendas of MSF Directors (Core Executive Committee) and international coordination platforms; 4) Influencing and setting agendas of Boards and Council;
•	Execute corporate change management assignments (e.g. culture change);
Responsible for steering on Responsible Behaviour policies, procedures, quality investigations and reporting & analytics, stimulating the desired culture change.

Achievements:
•	Setting up a Responsible Behaviour Unit that is developing a MSF OCA Integrity System and is in control of the case load 
•	Introduced new way of working based on bringing collective expertise and energy together 
Steered towards an inclusive, iterative and engaging Strategic Plan 2020-2024 process
•	Setting up an Executive Assistant Platform (self-steering) that has taken on the assignment of alignment, standardization and learning.
